Solution: 12-7-16 I checked Amag and ran a report and could see transactions from yesterday. I ran a status on the panel and found the super panel was offline. I reset the super panel and it came back online it was controllingredients panel 03 which has the two handicap reader's on it. I tested the readers and neither reader would work. I could send an unlock command to the door lock. I took a reader to the panel and it test good on both readers ports. I removed the entry reader from the pole and it started working. I cut away alot of extra reader wire and rewired the reader and remounted. Both readers are working now but the reader range is bad it takes about 15 seconds to get a read. I spoke with our Citrix Engineer yesterday , he told me they are receiving the tickets on the blank log on pads and have found out that the group that is adding the global groups  (iShop) are not running the  users profile through the TS update Script.  If we continue to get calls about blank log on pads, have them do the following:

1.	Launch IShop at http://www.ishop.delta.com
Enter your credentials.
2.	Go to Access/ID.
Select the Modify User Access.
Click on the Open Form(s) Button.
3.	Verify all the information on the Requestor Tab and then click the Next Button.
Fill in all required fields, then under the Secure Access Information type the the message Run ID through the TS Update Script.   Also indicate if its ECC (your regular SAP) or EWP ( New Warehouse access)  You can select Read-only.
4.	Click the Submit Button when the form(s) is complete and ready for submission.

If you need further assistance with this, please send an email to the IShop support group via email.  The address is ISHOP in outlook.

Name: MARIA MOURAO
Title: Needs help clearing cache to access LMS course
Description: Needs help clearing cache to access LMS course
Solution:
Agent received the text below and she is still receiving the same white screen...

Incident Description:
LMS course RCECOD100R you already enrolled and course already in progress using Delta issue workstation Customer Care  5 attempts....I advise user  to delete user temp files and cookies now getting a blank page only....please reset user profile under course ASAP!

Resolution/Action:
There was corrupt data in this course.  The data has been removed.  The lesson can be started again.  Before logging into the LMS, close all open applications and clear the cache on the computer by following these steps for IE 11:
1.     Go to your browser, DeltaNet, click on Tools on the menu bar, then Internet Options.
2.     On the General tab, under Browsing History, click on Delete.
3.     A Delete Browsing History dialog box will come up.
4.     Make sure the first four boxes are checked
a.     Preserve Favorites website data
b.    Temporary Internet Files and website data
c.     Cookies and website data
d.    History
e.     Download History
5.     Click Delete
6.     Make sure compatibility mode is set
a.     From the browser, select Tools from the menu bar or on the Command Bar, click Page
b.    Choose Compatibility View Settings
c.     Un-check both Display Intranet sites in Compatibility View and Use Microsoft compatibility list
d.    In the "Add this website" field add delta.com then click ADD
e.     In the "Add this website" field add pathlore.net then click ADD
f.     Click OK.

If you are on a managed set and cannot clear the cache, please log all the way out of the machine before launching the LMS again.  Please make sure you are taking the training on a computer setup for training.  Frontline and break room computers are not setup for training.  If you have dual monitors, turn one off when taking training.  Thanks!

Pathlore LMS Admin/ct

RCECOD100R - Customer Care Coding Recurent Training - - MSP - please reset user profile under course  10 min
013242400  Maria Mourao  maria.mourao@delta.com  MSP

**Title from related Incident record IM2852670:
Accessing Course ETops Basic course when accessing course and get to the assessment is showing white
Solution:
Related Incident IM2852670 closed.
Daron,
Ronald Whaley opened this incident with the IT helpdesk and does not have an email address in the Pathore LMS.  As Ronalds manager, would you share the information in the Resolution/Action section below?  Thanks!
Resolution/Action:
You have been reset for the assessment.  IE 11 requires this setting for courses to work properly in LMS.  Here are instructions for IE 11
1.	In Internet Explorer, Click Tools
2.	From the dropdown, click Compatibility View Settings
3.	From the pop up, un-check both "Display Intranet sites in Compatibility View" and "Use Microsoft compatibility list"
4.	In the "Add this website" field add delta.com then click ADD
5.	In the "Add this website" field add pathlore.net then click ADD
6.	Click Close and Log in to LMS as usual
Other Delta websites may not use Compatibility mode, so please reverse these settings when finished with LMS.

**Title from related Incident record IM2861705:
Issue with LMS - button used for accessing assessment unresponsive when clicked
Solution:
Related Incident IM2861705 closed.
You have been reset for the course.  IE 11 requires this setting for new courses to work properly in LMS.  Here are instructions for IE 11
1.	In Internet Explorer, Click Tools
2.	From the dropdown, click Compatibility View Settings
3.	From the pop up, un-check both "Display Intranet sites in Compatibility View" and "Use Microsoft compatibility list"
4.	In the "Add this website" field add delta.com then click ADD
5.	In the "Add this website" field add pathlore.net then click ADD
6.	Click Close and Log in to LMS as usual
Other Delta websites may not use Compatibility mode, so please reverse these settings when finished with LMS.

Name: KAITLYN EDGELL
Title: Keeps getting prompted login when access DeltaNet
Description: Keeps getting prompted login when access DeltaNet
Solution:
Clear entries in Credential Manager
Go to Start, Control Panel, Credential manager, Windows Credentials, Generic Credentials. Remove the one that says Microsoft_OC1:uir=xxxxx

Remove Crypto Folder
Trunk into machine \\machinename\c$ - to go folder that is under C:\programdata\microsoft\crypto\RSA and find the one that says S-1-5 and rename it or delete it

Change the registry entry in for Communicator Save Password
Go to Registry Editor (Start > Run > regedit > OK)
Choose

HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Communicator
Double-click the value SavePassword and set it to 0
Unlock users ID to make sure they are not locked, and then launch Lync

Name: SHEILA WALSON
Title: unable to access MPS activity window application
Description:
error message "your employee data record is not found, please contact your system supervisor" and user call manager who support the payroll group who advise user to have a ticket created with Delta IT helpdesk to report her issue ASAP!
**Title from related Incident record IM2872612:
unable to access MPS activity window application
Solution:
Related Incident IM2872612 closed.
The DL_PPR_NUM column value in the V_STF_MPS_MBR view for the employee has a different value, since normally it is the 9digit DELTA ID (0xxxxxx00) and the employee is a DGS employee and thus follows the 86xxxxxxxxx format for the column's value, and this value is what MPS Activity uses and compares to the employee profile's emp_nbr values. As a resolution, an EMPLOYEE, EMP_PROFILE and PDN_SYS_ASGNMT record values was added with EMP_NBR equal to the employee's V_STF_MPS_MBR.DL_PPR_NUM value.

*** *** There are no other related records.  Interaction closed by Incident IM2872612

unable to access lms course
Solution:
Related Incident IM2880408 closed.
You have been reset for the course.  If you are using a Delta computer, following these instructions:
1.	In Internet Explorer, Click Tools
2.	From the dropdown, click Compatibility View Settings
3.	From the pop up, un-check both "Display Intranet sites in Compatibility View" and "Use Microsoft compatibility list"
4.	In the "Add this website" field add delta.com then click ADD
5.	In the "Add this website" field add pathlore.net then click ADD
6.	Click Close and Log in to LMS as usual
Other Delta websites may not use Compatibility mode, so please reverse these settings when finished with LMS.

If you are using your personal computer and using the ExtraNet to login, follow these instructions:
The solution is to use the ACS Contractor link on the ExtraNet home page, do not log into the ExtraNet. Using this link will put you directly into the Pathlore LMS. The password for this is different than the Passport password.  Your current password is Delta1.  You will be asked to change it upon login.  You can take the training from there.

The work around options for the users are as following.

1)	User need to contact their ISP to  find out what is the work around to disable their DNS hijacking.
2)	Change the ISP provided router / broadband modem  client DHCP setting on DNS configuration to external DNS server like Google DNS 8.8.8.8

Name: FELESCITY GYNILD-CHANEY
Title: Page cannot be displayed access Delta.com
Description:
Page cannot be displayed access Delta.com

Cleared cache & cookies and ran gpupdate
Added to compatibility view
Restarted computer
Will not come up in IE nor but will finally open in FireFox after about 5 minutes logged in as the user or as Admin
here is no issue with Delta.com from my computer.

Noticed prompt for password so performed the following:
Clear entries in Credential Manager
Go to Start, Control Panel, Credential manager, Windows Credentials, Generic Credentials. Remove the one that says Microsoft_OC1:uir=xxxxx

Remove Crypto Folder
Trunk into machine \\machinename\c$ - to go folder that is under C:\programdata\microsoft\crypto\RSA and find the one that says S-1-5 and rename it or delete it

Change the registry entry in for Communicator Save Password
Go to Registry Editor (Start > Run > regedit > OK)
Choose

HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Communicator
Double-click the value SavePassword and set it to 0
Unlock users ID to make sure they are not locked, and then launch Lync

Title: VDI Machine is having issues accessing HPQC online
Description:
Both links for the application the user is utilizing result in an error where it refuses to download
http://www.qc.delta.com:8080/qcbin/start_a.jsp  and http://smspbdjdlap1027:8080/qcbin/start_a.jsp
Tried to clear out the user's cache files but this did not help matters at all
the error is as follows

Initialization has failed. Contact your system administrator.
For details, see the Loader log file.

Failure details:
http://smspbdjdlap1027:8080/qcbin/setup_a.cab - Failed to download this file. Error code 0x800C0008
**Title from related Incident record IM2914186:
VDI Machine is having issues accessing HPQC online
Solution:
Related Incident IM2914186 closed.
Helpdesk team,

Discussed with user and below was suggested as a further troubleshoot to fix this issue.QA Tools Admin won't have the ability to run the instructions with admin rights on users PC's.Advised user to reply back to the  mail communication sent to her if in case any further issues and we will assist accordingly.

the issue seems to be with downloading a required QC client component on the workstation.Since you were able to access QC before but recently encountering the issue,we suspect there could be a conflict of QC client components with any radia updates that has been received on the PC.In this case,you can follow up with the helpdesk to run through the below steps.
Note: QA Tools Admin team wont have the ability to remote into users workstation to run the below steps with admin rights.It has to be someone from the helpdesk team that needs to run with elevated rights.

Launch IE32 browser with admin rights (required only once) and enter the URL  : http://www.qc.delta.com:8080/qcbin/start_a.jsp which allows to load the required client components of QC
Once the login screen appears, then you can try login with your QC credentials. This basically allows to register the QC client components with your profile on the PC.
You can then try opening a IE32 bits browser without admin rights and load QC.

At times running a  GPUpdate /force command on the PC also helps to ensure policy has been properly applied and then relaunch QC with admin rights.This can also be checked by IT helpdesk team.

If the above didnt help,then they can run below steps

http://www.qc.delta.com:8080/qcbin/ALM-Platform-Loader.msi , download and install it first and try again launching QC with admin rights as mentioned above.

6)	Now close the browser, login again and trying accessing the app. This should resolve the issue.

Title: user unable to access tesseract
Description:
user unable to access tesseract
security authoriztion required
it doesn't allow user to log in cdv300 system monitor message cdi04  invaild action code
**Title from related Incident record IM2923083:
user says the tesseract system is currently down
Solution:
Related Incident IM2923083 closed.
As part of RFC C278260, settings were changed in CICS to allow mixed case data which caused issues with Tesseract and GEM-MIRS.  Both applications process only upper case data and prior to this change activity, CICS converted both lower and upper case character entries to upper case.  Once this issue was discovered, the CICS change in RFC C278260 was fallen back and the conversion capability was restored at 12:23 ET.

Name: COLIN DORSEY
Title: iCrew Access
Description:
I earlier contacted the help desk regarding access to iCrew.
I can now get in using the My tools portion of DeltaNet.
However if I go directly to icrew.delta.com or attempt to log in to iCrew Max or iCrew mobile I see that my account is locked out even though I just updated my password today.
Yes, i had an issue earlier where i reset it through iCrew, and that created a log error. we got that fixed through the register page.
AO - eCrew Please Advise
Thank you
**Title from related Incident record IM2943261:
iCrew Access
Solution:
Related Incident IM2943261 closed.
Tried to call the user, but got no answer, so I emailed him at the email addresses for him that were available to us.  Below is a copy of my email response.

Hi,

I was sorry to hear that you have been having troubles recently with iCrew access, passwords, etc.  I tried calling you, but received no answer, so Im sending this email in reply.  We received an incident which stated:

I earlier contacted the help desk regarding access to iCrew.
I can now get in using the My tools portion of DeltaNet.
However if I go directly to icrew.delta.com or attempt to log in to iCrew Max or iCrew mobile I see that my account is locked out even though I just updated my password today.
Yes, i had an issue earlier where i reset it through iCrew, and that created a log error. we got that fixed through the register page.
AO - eCrew Please Advise
Thank you

These issues are not unique to you, but we have been hearing a number of reports of pilots (and flight attendants) having password issues.  We also believe many are NOT having issues.  Approximately 400 crew members, on average, have an expiring password on any given day.  I understand that the Help Desk is receiving 10-12 calls per day regarding password problems, most of which sound similar to your issues.

The iCrew application has not changed, but a recent change occurred regarding passwords which we believe may have caused these issues.  The mainframe which runs in the background (for which iCrew is the GUI interface) was recently upgraded to accept Mixed Case passwords.  This was a necessary security improvement which Delta has wished to implement for years, and which was implemented on February 22.  Unfortunately, all of the various password systems within Delta are not yet completely coordinated in regard to requirements.  Some require mixed case, some require mixed case or all uppercase, and some allow any case.  We think that this has most likely interfered with password synchronization between systems in some cases.  It is my understanding that the password synchronization group is working on improving and ultimately correcting all synchronization issues, but I dont think everything has been corrected yet.

On the iCrew/mainframe side, the mainframe currently requires all uppercase letters (in addition to the 1 number which is required), or mixed case (and 1 number).  Typing in all lowercase letters in the iCrew password change function results in an Internal Server Error message, which is obviously not helpful, but not within our ability in iCrew to change.  When this occurs, no passwords have been changed.  In other cases, the password is correctly changed in iCrew, but it is not always properly synchronized to other systems.  There may also be cases in which synchronization does not occur properly when changing the password through other mechanisms.

Were sorry that some iCrew users are experiencing issues, and were trying to do our part to help alleviate the problems and get everything corrected.  The password synchronization group has the biggest piece of this process, and they are working on the issue as well.  As long as you have your password straightened out (which I hope is the case by now), or at least have the ability to log on to all Delta systems, all I can offer is to ask that you bear with us as the various groups at Delta with a stake in this issue work together to finalize a solution.  If you would like to communicate further with us about this issue, or about any iCrew issue, please feel free to respond to this email and we will get back to you when possible.  This mailbox (Feedback, iCrew) is monitored, but not every day, as it is not intended for urgent issues.

Hopefully, all of the password issues will be resolved in the near future.  Thank you for your patience.

Thanks,
Bill
iCrew Team

From: Citrix, Engineering
Sent: Tuesday, April 18, 2017 9:06 PM
To: Marie Hew (mhew@mltvacations.com)
Cc: Citrix, Engineering
Subject: IM2982833


Marie,

I have reviewed your incident ticket  From the information within the incident, it looks as though you looking for information and not having an actual incident.  Ill attempt to provide a flow for you to start the request process indicated in the incident.

Regarding your request, you are trying to set up a new user with access to Citrix and email.  As part of the Citrix team, we do not work too much with regards to setting up a Delta email address.  I believe that both the Citrix and Email access is requested using the IShop Process within Delta.

Providing that you are able to submit IShop requests, you would logon  to https://ishop.delta.com using your Passport ID.  Once logged on, you would complete and submit the appropriate form to request access.

I took a look at the IShop page and think that the following selections would be a good starting point

	Email -  Expand the New Hire / Transfers section of the form  Select the Create / Delete Users Delta Email Address and click the green Open Forms button.  Complete the form and submit.
	Citrix Access - Expand the Access / IDs section of the form  Select the Modify Users Access form and click the green Open Forms button.  You may be able to use the Modify Users Access form under the New Hires / Transfers section as well  Complete the form and Submit.

Note:  In both scenarios, do not be afraid to use the Comments section to expand on the request that you are looking for  In other words, be as descriptive as you can  If you know the Citrix groups that the user needs, include those in the request as well.  An example of the comments section might be Please configure user 123456 for TSGuest Access and add the user to the ATL_RCCTSSAPApps global group 

The following represents a sampling of some different Citrix groups along with the applications that are associated with the group

ATL_RCCTSSAPApps 	SAP
ATL_RCCTSHyperion	Hyperion Web v11 (Brio)
ATL_RCCTSRightSite	Documentum Webtop
CtxSmartView		SmartView in Excel
CtxOffice2010		Office Suite (This requires that the user has a Delta MSOffice license).

As this incident does not really reflect an issue, I have marked the IMPACTED ENDED and will close the incident tomorrow. If you have any questions or concerns, please reply to this email.

Thanks

Chris Shriner

I reviewed the incident that you opened  From what I understand, you are indicating that you now longer have access to Access 2010 in Citrix. I checked your Windows ID and it does not appear that you are entitled to Microsoft Access.  I see that you are a member of the ATL_RCCTSSAPApps and ATL_RCCTSOffice2007 global groups.  The ATL_RCCTSOffice2007 group only provides access to Microsoft Excel and Word in Citrix.  I also checked our logs to see if you had launched Access during the last week but could not find any launches.

If you have a requirement for Access in Citrix, you will need to submit an IShop request to get access to the CtxOfice2010 global group.  This would provide you access to the suite of products.

Since access is not granted as part of an incident, I am closing this incident using this email

Thanks

Chris

I was concerned there were other sub-domains that get launched within the delta.com<http://delta.com> site but Ive asked our network/security team to check why allowing delta.com<http://delta.com> domain would not also allow subdomains.

There are additional changes coming up on our end so we will be on alert for any reported issues and we will do some testing on our end as well. Unfortunately, our IT Maintenance and Engineering team does not have access to all Delta modules so we could only check those links we had access to.

Thanks,
Misti

On the up side, HA has rolled back this change so the PC is now working as it did before and the issue has been temporarily resolved. Offshore Student Login Procedure

Prerequisites	You must have access to Internet Explorer 9.0 (IE 9.0) or higher.

Procedure	Follow the steps below to login to LMS.

1.	Access the Delta Extranet: deltanet.delta.com  .
a.	Do NOT sign in with your PPR or password!

a.	In the User ID field, type your PPR number (nine digits).  The default LMS password is DeltaMMDD, where MMDD is your birth month and day.  You will be prompted to change the password. Name: DOUGLAS DIAMOND
Title: Unable to access Citrix for External user access
Description:
Unable to access Citrix for External user access
External ID: ICR567001
Shows error:  Attempting to open Sandbox JAR and has the Citrix HTTPS:\\NFUSE.DELTA.COM\CITRIX\METAFRAME\CLIENTS\JAVA\JICA-COREN.JAR as a trusted libary
**Title from related Incident record IM3017647:
Unable to access Citrix for External user access
Solution:
Related Incident IM3017647 closed.
** Received verification from  the user that are is working.

Sent user the following email...  Ending the impact as the user is off work today and will not be able to act on the email until he returns to the office...

_____________________________________________
From: Citrix, Engineering
Sent: Friday, May 19, 2017 11:31 AM
To: 'ddiamond@icrr255x.com'
Cc: Citrix, Engineering
Subject: IM3017647


As discussed, I am following up on our conversation with this email

In our conversation, you mentioned that you are launching your Citrix applications using the external Web Interface (https://nfuse.delta.com).  From the description of the incident, you are receiving problems while accessing your applications.  This is due to the fact that nfuse.delta.com is not running in compatibility mode and is falling back to the Java client.

To resolve the issue, there are a couple options

1.	Add delta.com to the compatibility view  If you are using a non-managed workstation, you can add delta.com to the compatibility view settings by following the steps below:
a.	Launch IE 11
b.	Click on the Tools Option >> select Compatibility View settings
c.	Enter delta.com in the Websites to Add box and click ADD.  This should move delta.com to the websites added section of the dialog.
d.	Click OK to close the Compatibility View dialog.
e.	Close IE 11.
f.	Go through the process to access your Citrix applications.

You may need to completely remove and reinstall the Citrix Receiver client if the compatibility viewer does not work

1.	Open Control Panel >> Programs and Features >> Remove the Citrix client (if installed)  The Citrix client may be represented by Citrix Receiver, Citrix Online Plugin, or Presentation Server Client.  There is a Citrix Receiver Removal Utility that can be used to completely remove the registry settings  This utility can be downloaded from https://support.citrix.com/article/CTX137494  -- you may need to create an account to download.
2.	Reboot the server.
3.	Logon to the workstation using Administrator privileges.
4.	Open a web browser and navigate to http://receiver.citrix.com
5.	Download the Citrix Receiver  I would not install through the browser, just save the file at this point.
6.	Open the folder location where the Citrix Receiver install was saved
7.	Right click on the Citrix Receiver Install file and select to Run as Administrator to install.

Please reply back with any test results and additional information.  I have left the incident open until your comments are received

Thanks

Chris Shriner

Name: MELISSA GIFFORD
Title: Issue accessing Deltanet
Description:
Solution for accessing Deltanet on an Android device using Google as the browser:
1.	Select the 3 vertical dots in the top-right corner of the screen
2.	Select Privacy
3.	Scroll down & select Clear Browsing Data
4.	Once everything clears, have the user go to deltanet.delta.com
(The user will get an error saying their connection isnt private)
5.	Have the user tap on Advanced
6.	Click on the link that says Proceed to apps.delta.com
(The page will redirect to the same exact page again)
7.	Have them click on the Proceed to apps.delta.com link again
8.	That should do the trick; the user should be seeing the Deltanet login page
If not, reach out a Team Lead.
Solution:
